{
  "texts": [
    "While human reviewers took approximately 100 hours to complete the reviews, Mistral LLM completed the same task in just 17 hours, showcasing a fourfold increase in efficiency.",
    "This dramatic reduction in review time does not compromise the quality of the initial analysis, making Mistral LLM an invaluable tool for conducting preliminary literature reviews at scale.",
    "The implications of this efficiency are profound, suggesting that Mistral LLM can free up valuable time for researchers, allowing them to focus on deeper, more complex aspects of their studies.",
    "As the technology continues to evolve, it is anticipated that the integration of LLMs into the review process will become increasingly seamless, offering even greater benefits in terms of efficiency and scalability.",
    "DiscussionThis section interprets the results, discusses their implications, and how they fit into the broader context of existing literature."
  ]
}